text.paragraph:
Because of the varied response of pediatric patients to CNS-acting drugs, therapy should be initiated with the lowest dose and increased as required (see 



                              DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
                           ).

Since clinical experience with Chlordiazepoxide hydrochloride in pediatric patients under 6 years of age is limited, use in this age group is not recommended. Hyperactive aggressive pediatric patients should be monitored for paradoxical reactions to Chlordiazepoxide hydrochloride (see 



                              PRECAUTIONS
                           ).
